The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Upper Ganges Sugar amp; Industries Ltd will raise Rs 68.29 crore through issue of 45.52 lakh equity shares on rights basis. The board of directors have approved the issue of rights shares of Rs 10 each for cash at a price of Rs 150 per share aggregating to Rs 68.29 crore in the ratio of 13 shares for every 20 shares held, the company informed the Bombay stock exchange. 

 The China Banking Regulatory Commission has approved Allahabad Bank to open its representative office at Shenzhen, China. The bank has already received Reserve Bank of India?s approval for opening a branch at Hong Kong and a representative office at Shenzhen.

 Shivalik Global Ltd will enter the market to raise Rs 60 crore to part finance its new readymade manufacturing unit and other capital expenditures. The net offer to public will be of 70 lakh equity shares.

 Lafarge has been included on the 2006 list for 100 most sustainable corporations in the world. This is for the second year running that Lafarge has made to the list since its launch in 2005.

 Pfizer Ltd has launched Lyrica,which is an advanced treatment for the management of neuropathic pain. The drug was tested on over 10000 patients in a clinical research program. 

 Uttam Galva Steels has won a $170 million order from Stemcor to supply cold rolled, galvanised and colour coated steel over three years. Uttam Galva will fix the price of its products every quarter.

 The Actavis Group, headquartered in Iceland, has set up a campus for its subsidiary Lotus Labs at Koramangala in Bangalore. The new premises will house offices, laboratories and facilities for clinical studies.

 Rohit Ferro-Tech Ltd will introduce an initial public offer to part finance the Ferro Alloy Unit at Jajpur in Orissa.

